.TH FOLLOW 1 "2012 Feb 28"

.SH NAME
\fBfollow\fR \(en standalone version of \fBtail -f\fR

.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBfollow\fR \fIFILENAME\fR

.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBfollow\fR is a standalone version of \fBtail(1) -f\fR which echoes
the whole file before it starts to follow.

It outputs data which was appended to the specified file as the file
grows.  This can, for example, be useful when monitoring log files.

.SH OPTIONS
.PP
.I FILENAME
.RS
The filename of the file which should be followed.
.RE

